deck_description: This is decks core is a Sky Striker archetype. However my twist on it is to protect your spells / traps with Artifact cards to be able to get easy backup defense/offense cards. Please remember to give me feedback so that i may improve this deck and all future deck builds. :D

deck_excerpt: The deck’s strength comes from exploiting the effect of Gladiator Beast Secutor in tandem with all the other (old and new) Gladiator Beast cards. Che
deck_description: The main strategy for this deck is to summon Secutor to the field (either by the effect of Test Tiger or any other GB monster), and then start swarming the field with his effect at the end of each battle phase. Ideally, you want Secutor remaining on the field indefinitely but even if you’re only able to resolve his effect once: It can put you so far ahead of your opponent that it’s essentially a win-condition by itself. Another important part of this deck is the Respite engine: Comprising of the card itself, Gladiator Proving Ground and every other card in the deck that has “Gladiator Beast” in its name. They synergize together to make the deck flow easily and consistently, by allowing you to filter through your deck to get to your key cards faster; while also greatly reducing your chances of bricking by allowing you to “reload” your hand if necessary. As with all the other GB cards, Respite can be looped back to your hand via the effect of Equeste, allowing you to re-use Respite multiple times in a single duel. Secutor’s effect can snowball in numerous way: Whether it’s by going +4 through summoning 2x Equeste and resolving both of their effects; or by using the monsters summoned by him to make the Fusion monster Gyzarus, or the Link monster Dragacius. I hope you find the video below helpful in understanding the sort of combos you can do with him, along with the rest of the deck: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ANOY_eC6UGQ Thank you for reading!

deck_excerpt: I will be stunned if Secret Village doesn't go to zero by next format.
deck_description: Pretty standard Altergeist build mixed in with the Spellbook Engine & Secret Village of the Spellcasters. Just about any hand that opens with Secret Village/Terraforming, Multifaker & ANY trap card is likely going to be auto-win, especially against Sky Strikers. I also splashed in a copy of Silent Magician on account of it being a pretty formidable beatstick under the right circumstances; something this deck BADLY needs against Inspect Border & Majesty's Fiend. And to top it off, it side decks 3 copies of Red Reboot in the likely event of a Paleozoic or a mirror match. Let me know what you guys think.

deck_excerpt: A deck based on fusion summoning and using affects and spell cards to your advantage to overcome anything your opponent sets up.
deck_description: Utilize Fusion Sage, Blazeman, and Woodsman to gather polymerization, then summon fusions. Start with Nova Master to continue to increase hand size or use Adoration's, Gaia's, or Great Tornado's effect to lower enemy attack. Use Absolute Zero for monster wipes. Plasma Vice to take down dangerous monsters or set monsters. Use Shadowmist's ability to fusion summon and draw any HERO from your deck. Use Hero Mask and Prisma's ability to set up for powerful fusions. Use Necroshade to fusion summon Escuridao and then normal summon BladeEdge for no tribute. And these are just a few strategies that this deck can dish out at anytime.

deck_excerpt: Odd-Eyes: The deck that does what Magicians do, but with prettier colours. Teach your opponents the value of smiles while beating them to death with a
deck_description: This deck aims to summon Electrumite pre-Pendulum and gain advantage with Arc Pendulum and the aforementioned Electrumite. Incorporates a small Magician engine to take advantage of the 3x Duelist Alliance. Remember to summon Dissolver to fusion summon Vortex Dragon, as this makes him able to be re-summoned later. If not, Absolute Dragon being linked away offers a backdoor way to access him.  If you don't own/don't wish to run Electrumite, here's what I recommend to replace her:  Cut the Supreme King Dragon Darkwurm, the Supreme King Gate Zero, the Dragon Shrines and the Foolish Burials, along with the two Electrumite in the ED. Replace those main deck cards with 2x Pendulum Dragon, 1x Lancer Dragon, 1x Xiangke Magician, 1x Odd-Eyes Fusion, 1x Persona Dragon and 1x Mirage Dragon. The two Electrumites can be replaced with an Odd-Eyes Raging Dragon or Odd-Eyes Rebellion Dragon (food for OE Fusion) and another link such as Underclock Taker or Space Insulator.  Shoutouts to TeamSalmonYGO.

deck_excerpt: Join the Cipher Lords & Grab this deck & give it a spin! I update it every day or every week!
deck_description:
We are the Neo Galaxy-Eyes!

I am here to teach you how to use this intergalactic army or as humans call them a "Deck" this army is a Work in progress so I will be updating this "Deck" a lot so make sure to check back to me every week!

Here is a list of some combinations of "Cards" I've been testing out BUT! These are not complete! New "Cards" are being made as we speak!
Code words: NS [ Normal Summon ] SS [ Special Summon ] XS [ XYZ Summon ] Eff [ Activate a Card Effect ] Add [ Add a card to your hand ]

First Turn:

Just play the deck because first turn isn't the best for setup for this deck!

Second Turn:

Early-Game Combo:

Have in your hand: Galaxy Soldier & Any LIGHT monster [ That you don't need in this combo ] & Photon Vanisher & Galaxy Expedition
Eff Galaxy Soldier SS It, Eff Galaxy Soldier [ When it's SS'ed you can add a "Galaxy" Monster to your hand ] Add Galaxy-Eyes Cloudragon then, use Galaxy Expedition and SS Galaxy Knight then, SS Photon Vanisher using his Effect and Add Galaxy-Eyes Photon Dragon then, NS Galaxy-Eyes Cloudragon use it's effect to SS your Galaxy-Eyes Photon Dragon from your hand then, you have a couple options!

Option 1:

If your opponent got a good hand and is completely set up XS either Number 90: Galaxy-Eyes Photon Lord or Number 38: Hope Harbinger Dragon Titanic Galaxy [ Photon Lord for Monsters & being unable to be destroyed my card effects. And Titanic Galaxy for Spells, Traps & Monsters ]

Option 2:

If your opponent got a bad/neutral hand and is barely set up or have any hand traps XS either Galaxy-Eyes Cipher Dragon then XS into Galaxy-Eyes Cipher Blade Dragon or [ If the situation calls for it & you have it in your hand you can XS! the almighty, Neo Galaxy-Eyes Cipher Dragon! using Rank-Up-Magic: Cipher Ascension! ] or Number 62: Galaxy-Eyes Prime Photon Dragon or Number 107: Galaxy-Eyes Tachyon Dragon

Late-Game Combo:

This combo is very good for stalling when you need cards but you need a really specific field...

First, you need: a Field with Number 90: Galaxy-Eyes Photon Lord, then you need to be losing with less LP than your opponent & have a lot of "Galaxy" monsters in your graveyard.

Use the Effect of Number 90: Galaxy-Eyes Photon Lord [ He can add a "Photon or "Galaxy" to him as material or to your hand. When it says: "Add this card to your hand?" after you choose a card say "Yes" to add it to your hand and "No" to add it as material ] Add Galaxy Mirror Sage to your hand then set him face down. When it's your opponents turn make sure they attack the face down, when they do u will be able to use the Effect of Galaxy Mirror Sage and you gain loads of LP and when it's destroyed & sent to the grave [ After being flipped face up ] you can SS a LVL 4 or under "Galaxy" monster from the grave. Now if you have a Galaxy Mirror Sage in your grave you can SS it FACE DOWN! so you can keep doing this combo forever! [ Though if you don't have another Galaxy Mirror Sage in your grave just do the same combo next turn ]

The End for now...

And thats all that I have thought of but I will be updating this all the time! and I hope you check this out, Leave a like, and try to get to popular decks this week!

WE DID IT!

We got to POPULAR DECKS THIS WEEK!

THANKS FOR ALL THE SUPPORT!

And do not worry! I will still be updating this deck all the time!

You guys are all the best!

Thank you! :D

It also has many powerful monsters, with a combination of Yuya Sakaki's, Yusaku Fujiki/Playmaker's, and Zarc. It has Supreme King monsters, Performapal monsters, and most important of all, Odd-Eyes monsters. I like to chip away life points, then finish with a powerful monster. Odd-Eyes Pendulum Dragon's double damage effect also comes into play for this strategy.

deck_description: A work in progress deck.  Any suggestions more than welcome.  I've always had fun using the low level beast monsters to swarm the field.  Particularly the Baby Raccoons and Ronin Raccoon.  I figured a fast swarm deck style could be great for the new link format in order to get link monsters out quicker, so I decided that I'd start experimenting a bit.  I decided to incorporate a card that I love but I never see get used, "Double Summon".  When play testing, this card let me summon out two rescue cats which in turn let me bring out four beast and start doing some link summoning on turn one and still have a "Solemn Judgment" and a "Dark Bribe" left in my hand to set.  The upcoming Palladions are very interesting to me so I decided to try putting some in here and see how they work with this deck.  Once again, this is an experimental, work in progress deck.  Please leave your suggestions for me so I can improve this deck.

The main strategy of this deck is to get an OTK with Frighfur Sabre-Tooth and Kraken. Here's the OTK: (You want to go second)
  1. Use things like Patchwork, King of the Swamp, and Bear to get 2 Polymerization into your hand.
  2. Fusion Summon Kraken.
  3. Use Kraken's effect to destroy a monster on your opponent's field (if they summoned last turn)
  4. Use the 2nd Polymerization to Fusion Summon Sabre-Tooth
  5. Use Sabre-Tooth's effect, which will bring Kraken back into the field.
  6. Enter the Battle Phase.
  7. Because of Sabre-Tooth's effect, his attack will be 2800, and Kraken's will be 2600
  8. Since your opponent has no monsters (preferably), attack directly
  9. Attack with Sabre-Tooth, 8000 - 2800 = 5200
  10. Attack with Kraken, 5200 - 2600 = 2600
  11. Kraken's effect allows him to attack twice. 2600 - 2600 = 0
  12. GG!

deck_excerpt: very good blue eyes deck (it blows these other blue eyes decks out of the water, pretty much making them worthless)
deck_description: blue eyes are one of the most versatile decks in yugioh, so far. this deck is even better than the others though. it's a guaranteed good first hand as long as you know what you're doing with it. because the first hand is always random there is really no way to make a good strategy guide for this deck. all i can do for you is tell you how to get out either true king or crystal wing (they have the same requirements) with what you have. what's best is if you use a glow-up bulb and synchro it with any level 8 monster into blue-eyes spirit dragon, use glow-up's effect to bring it back onto the field, now you have to choose whether you want true king or crystal wing.  if you chose true king: use spirit's effect to bring out stardust spark, synchro that and glow-up (or another lvl 1 tuner) into cloudcastle, use cloudcastle's effect to special summon spirit from the graveyard, xyz summon true king.  if you chose crystal wing: use spirit's effect to bring out moonlight, synchro moonlight and glow-up (or another lvl 1 tuner) into crystal wing.  other than that you'll just have to adjust your strategy for what the battle calls for.  plus it's good in both link and mr3 (both strategies work exactly the same in link and in mr3)  hope this helped  ps. i would love to hear your opinions on how to make this deck better

I've been spending a lot of time trying to make use of Superancient Deepsea King Coelecanth and this is one of the more unique lists I've come up with.  The biggest issues I've run into while trying to use Coelecanth are the reliance on normal summons and a lack of good search tools.  Brilliant Fusion into Seraphinite and Baobaboon with Dragonic Diagram are there to remedy these problems while also providing a possible win condition with Metaltron XII.  If this deck works properly, it can deal well over 8000 points of damage in one turn.  The current list is a bit bricky atm but I will continue to tweak it.  I will also add a side deck once I am happy with the main deck.  I know this deck looks messy, but I swear there was a reason for each card at some point.  If people would like a more detailed explanation of the strategy and card choices, just let me know.  I am also open to suggestions for card changes, make sure to indicate which card(s) would be removed for any new additions.

After way more testing with Altergeists this is the build I came up with. It performed extremely well in testing and I was able to go 6-0 on Ygopro using this deck. I had to edit the ratios so much over the course of the past two weeks and this is the final product! Also my last Altergeist build messed up and the file can't be downloaded for whatever reason so sorry about that. The goal of this deck is to go first and set traps and then use them next turn to trigger Altergeist Multifaker and blow up the field with Altergeists and interruptions. I added Ghost Reaper & Winter Cherries to the main deck because it stops the current meta decks completely by having meta Cherry targets in the extra deck like Heavymetalfoes Electrumite for pendulums, Spyral Double Helix for Spyrals, etc... Also there is Raidraptor - Ultimate Falcon in the extra deck. That is a Cherries target for Raidraptors, but it's mainly for the side deck card Waking The Dragon. During game two, if your opponent sides properly they will want to destroy your backrow since Altergeists rely on backrow. You can set Waking The Dragon and when they destroy it, you can summon Raidraptor - Ultimate Falcon and then you win the game because Ultimate Falcon is almost impossible to deal with since it can only be Kaijud or destroyed by battle. One really cool combo going first to help you if you're new to Altergeists is if you draw Altergeist Meluseek going first and you didn't draw Multifaker, you can normal summon Meluseek and then link into Linkuriboh and use Meluseek's effect to add Multifaker to your hand! Enjoy the deck.

deck_excerpt: Wipe your opponents entire board with ease with the fires of Armageddon in this Unorthodox deck.
deck_description: Armageddon is a OTK deck with two possible methods of OTKing your opponent. I'll try to make this as brief as possible. Dozered: The first possible OTK is This hand. Manju, Ritual/or/Demise, and Megamorph and Doom Dozer. if the opponent is not running Monster Effect counters you can wipe the board with Demise's effect Taking 2000LP and more than likely leaving you with less health then your opponent. When you ritual summon if you have Doom Dozer in hand send both Neo Bug and Insect Knight to the graveyard. this allows you to SS Doom Dozer. Once you've finished this apply Megamorph to Doom Dozer and BOOM you got an OTK. Blue Eyes: The second method is to Have Manju, Ritual/or/Demise, Megamorph, and Swing of Memories the same pattern applies as above however instead of sacrificing Insects you sacrifice Blue-Eyes White Dragon. Once you've cleared the board use Swing of Memories and bring Blue eyes back. then apply Megamorph and once again you've got an OTK. I've played around 50 games with this deck and it has run though its Great games and its bad games. If any players have any suggestions please leave a comment and i will overview it. Thanks a lot Blason!

deck_excerpt: This Special Atlantean Mermail deck had proven to be one of the stable ones. Use the Toad, Kaiju, F.A. Dawn, and Tri-gate Wizard to negate ur opponent
deck_description:
Please read the deck description below as certain combos are quite complicated. Advices for the Deck The deck is not fixed. If you want to have a lower chance of brick, you could well take away one Atlantean Marksman and one Atlantean Heavy Infantry and add in Surface or Aqua Spirit. These cards also help control the graveyard to summon Moulinglacia. The same goes for adding a few cards to prevent ur opponent from disrupting ur combo. Take away Infantry and Marksman (if you think 3 terraforming is too bricky, take away one) and add in Called by the Grave or Twin Twisters or Cosmic Cyclone. Two Abyss-Scales equip spell cards are also applicable, as it adds extra protection and makes OTK real easy if you equip it to Mermail Abyssmegalo. Adding one copy of Dupe Frog seems to also work as Toadally Awesome would be able to summon a fixed Attack target next Standby Phase, and the Dupe Frog would be able to search for the last Swap Frog if it was sent from the field to the graveyard, and potentially bring back Toadally Awesome again. But I personally find the card bricky in certain cases and didn't add it. Remember you can edit the deck according to ur play style. Combo 1 Neptabyss, the Atlantean Prince + Mermail Abyssteus
  1. Summon the prince, use effect to throw Atlantean Dragoons into the grave.
  2. Dragoon search for a Mermail Abyssmegalo and Prince search for another Atlantean Dragoons
  3. Summon Mermail Abyssteus by throwing away Atlantean Dragoons into the grave
  4. Atlantean Dragoons search for Moulinglacia the Elemental Lord, Mermail Abyssteus search for Mermail Abyssgunde
  5. Summon Riplodocus using Prince and Abyssteus
  6. Summon Abyssmegalo by throwing Abyssgunde and a random water monster into the grave (leave the spot below Riplodocus open)
  7. Abyssgunde effect revives Abyssteus
  8. You have 5 water monsters in the grave, so summon Moulinglacia below Riplodocus
  9. Use Riplodocus effect to change Moulinglacia type to dinosaur
  10. Summon Summon Sorceress using Riplodocus and Moulinglacia
  11. Summon Number 42: Galaxy Tomahawk under Summon Sorceress
  12. Use Tomahawk effect to summon 4 token
  13. Use 2 token to make Proxy Dragon
  14. Use Tomahawk and 1 token to make Knightmare Goblin beside the Proxy Dragon
  15. Activate Goblin effect throw away one card and draw one, and then normal summon a random monster next to Goblin
  16. Use Goblin and the random monster to summon a Trigate Wizard
  17. Use Summon Sorceress effect to summon Knightmare Corruptor Iblee (because it's pointing to Proxy Dragon)
  18. Use Iblee and Summon Sorceress to summon Knightmare Gryphon
  19. Iblee will be summoned on ur opponent's field
  20. If you prefer, use Gryphon to bring back any spell cards from the grave
  21. Remember the last token? Use that to summon Link Spider above the Trigate Wizard
  22. You must also realise that this combo work best when it's a 3 card combo, to make Proxy Dragon work you must have another monster next to it. So for example if you had a swap frog in ur hand, you could normal summon it using Goblin, it throws Ronintoadin into the grave, link it away, and it gives you an extra Ronintoadin available to summon next to the Proxy Dragon.
  Combo 2 Terraforming (or Kyoutou Waterfront) + Destrudo the Lost Dragon's Frisson + any monster you can normal summon with (not Deep Sea Diva or Ronintoadin)
  1. Activate Terraforming to search for Kyoutou Waterfront and activate that.
  2. Normal summon the monster
  3. summon Destrudo by activating its effect
  4. Summon Yazi, Evil of the Yang Zing
  5. Use Yazi effect to pop one opponent card
  6. summon Mare Mare
  7. Mare Mare effect to summon 3 token
  8. Summon Linkuriboh and Link Spider
  9. Use the 4 monsters to summon Saryuja Skull Dread
  10. Skull Dread draws
  11. Use Waterfront to search for Kaiju
  12. Skull Dread special summons the Kaiju
  13. You will find most times in this combo that you will be able to summon other monsters due to Skull Dread's drawing effect. Such as an extra Toadally Awesome if you managed to draw Swap Frog. Dawn Dragster is also possible to summon next turn as Destrudo is in the graveyard.
Combo 3 Swap Frog + any water monster
  1. use frog effect to rid of the water monster, summon the frog and throw Ronintoadin into the graveyard.
  2. Bounce frog back and normal summon it again
  3. frog effect throw another swap frog into the grave
  4. use Ronintoadin effect get it back on the field
  5. Summon Toadally Awesome
Combo 4 (OTK combo) Neptabyss, the Atlantean Prince + (Optional) Mermail Abyssteus or Mermail Abyssmegalo The one card combo works when you have Prince and 3 other water monsters in hand. If you have another Abyssteus or Abyssmegalo in hand, it would be a lot easier to carry out the combo.
  1. summon Prince, use effect to throw Atlantean Dragoons into the grave
  2. Prince search for another Dragoons, Dragoons search for Abyssmegalo
  3. Summon Abyssmegalo by throwing Dragoons and another random water monster from hand
  4. Dragoon search for another Abyssmegalo
  5. Summon Abyssmegalo by throwing away 2 random water monsters
  6. Use Abyssmegalo effect to attack twice by tributing Prince
  7. Prince effect activates and revives Atlantean Dragoons
  8. now you have 9000 worth of damage, enough to OTK ur opponent
  9. This combo improves a lot if you have Abyss-Scale equip spell cards in the deck. I didn't include it in this deck as this deck is mainly focused on bringing monsters that can negate ur opponent. But if you want to OTK, consider adding Abyss-Scale cards into the deck (usually one  Cetus,  one Mizuchi)

deck_excerpt: Pure Abyss Actor OTK Deck 2018 (Post Mellow Madonna)
deck_description: Upon special requests to make this deck, I have been testing Abyss Actors from scratch and this deck is very casual but can go up against tier two decks without losing. I normally do not upload OCG based decks or decks with OCG cards in them since I live in the USA and want to stick to the current meta game we have in the TCG. I have found this Pure Abyss Actor deck to be fun to play and there are many combos hidden within the deck to be discovered for people who are trying this specific deck for the first time. The combos involve the Abyss Actor cards themselves and the extra deck monsters, especially Heavymetalfoes Electrumite. This deck utilizes all of the Abyss Actor monsters and the Abyss Actor spell cards with no other pendulum monsters in the deck since it is Pure Abyss Actors. Making a build that relies on summoning Heavymetalfoes Electrumite going first and setting up interruptions could be a good meta deck once the new Abyss Actor cards come out in the TCG. I have found this deck to be most effective going second because you can actually OTK your opponent on that second turn! One cool combo I love in this deck is when you're going second and your opponent has a monster and you have none while you have Abyss Actor - Curtain Raiser or Abyss Actor - Extras in your hand. You can summon one, or both of those monsters and then normal summon if you only special summoned one of the two to make Electrumite and send Abyss Actor - Wild Hope off Electrumite's effect. Then, you activate a scale and pop it using Electrumite's effect to add Wild Hope back to your hand and draw one. Next, activate Wild Hope in scale and any other Abyss Actor monster for the other scale and use Wild Hope's effect to make the other scale a nine scale. Lastly, pendulum summon four or five monsters and OTK! I love this combo because your opponent just gets OTKd out of nowhere and it's very funny. Hope you enjoy the deck and have fun figuring out all the other fun combos!
x
Watch how to use this deck in YGO Lite (Youtube).  Link : https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=jY8pJXRm69U&feature=youtu.be

After months of testing via trial and error, I found (and hopefully wasn't the only one) a way to make Mekk-knight summons even better. When the Dark Saviors set came out this year, it introduced Vampires, Brandish (Sky Striker Aces), and Skyfang Brigade (Fur Hire). To make things simpler I decided to test out the Mekk-Knight build with the Brandish engine and found out that its actually really consistent in terms of summons. As long as the main field is empty you can spam the brandish spells to get your monsters on the field to special summon the Mekk-knight of your choice and continue the chain. Only problem is whether or not you can get the cards to get that said chain started. If you think this deck is still inconsistent feel free to alter the card list to suit your play-style...  I will give a bit of advice; once you get the sky striker of your choice on field, try to get the link-2 Mekk-Knight Morning Star on field to have a bit of advantage. Outside of that, I hope you enjoy...

Just type Spyral Knightmare combos on YouTube and you will find a good video that will help you. Or, if you know Spyrals really well then you should have no problem playing the deck. deck_description:
Hope you guys enjoy this Deck. Super Quantum cards have Unique abilities to Summon / Shuffle from grave / or add to hand This combos well with their XYZ counter parts the Super Quantal Beasts. Super Quantal Beasts are able to use their effects for effective board control not only that but the stat lining is no joke either. In order of my favorites:

Super Quantal Mech Beast Magnaliger: I thoroughly enjoy this card not only for his effect of destroying any monster on the board but his stat lining combined with Magnaslayer can cause an OTK

Super Quantal Mech Beast Grampulse: Second we have Grampulse with his ability for removing any Spell/Trap on the field with a rather sturdy defense it won't be going anywhere soon in combat.

Super Quantal Mech Beast Aeroboros: Aerboros is my least favorite due to a Moderate stat lining and a sub par Effect Change a monster to face down Defense.

Once you have used all three Super Quantal Mech Beasts  you'll be able to summon you're boss monster Super Quantal Mech King Great Magnus: if you're able to get this monster onto the field you're guaranteed the win. Any recommendations or change please leave a comment! -Sorry for the brief Analysis got a party to attend to!

deck_excerpt: This deck started out as a joke deck with roughly 37 dog-themed monster cards and 3 Where Arf Thou?'s. Since then, it's evolved to be a legitimately p
deck_description: This deck started out as a joke deck with roughly 37 dog-themed monster cards and 3 Where Arf Thou?'s. Since then, it's evolved to be a legitimately playable deck outside of the current meta. Now, the deck is built around using Flamvell Firedog's effect to special summon other fire monsters with under 200 DEF, these mainly being the 6* Hazy Flame Cerberus and the 4* Diceclops. XYZ summoning with Diceclops and Firedog allows you access to huge staples, such as Number 39: Utopia and Gagagigo the Risen. Using Firedog's effect to summon Cerberus ends up with an XYZ summon of Gauntlet Launcher instead. (there aren't a lot of dog XYZs.) Where Arf Thou? is still in the deck, mainly used to summon Slacker Magician in one turn using Outstanding Dog Marron as material. This can be done easily with Double Summon.

deck_excerpt: Use tokens to link summon and enable high rank xys plays
deck_description: The main strategy of the deck is to use Mecha Phantom Beast Raiten to discard cards to summon tokens, one of which being Mecha Phantom Beast O-Lion allowing you to normal summon any of the other level 4 Mecha Phantom Beasts. Use 2 of the tokens summoned to link summon Greatfly, then as long as you have one token on the field, you can xyz summon Mecha Phantom Beast Dracossack. From there you can do what you want. Also the Windwitch engine is there for added consistency and defensive plays with Crystal Wing Synchro Dragon.
Check my video  https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GiBAYI3_dzY&feature=youtu.be

deck_excerpt: Fill the board with at least 3 mekk-knights to start off with world legacy cards negating everything left and right with memory and purple nightfall b
deck_description: Mainly, go second. use memory to search for a purple nightfall use his effect to get blue sky. Use blue sky's effect to get avram and if you can get a second mekk then get a indigo eclipse (grab any mekk-knight useful after indigo eclipse). Summon avram and go into morning star with avram and blue sky. Use morning star's effect to get a world legacy card preferably secret if you do not have it already in your hand. Then summon your other mekk-knights to the field with indigo first.

deck_excerpt: A counter-attack sweep style deck build around Red-Eyes Black Flare Dragon and Red-Eyes Black Dragon Sword.
deck_description: This deck is build around stalling using Red-Eyes Baby Dragon and Masked Dragon to bring out Red-Eyes Black Flare Dragon and use it affect to destroy weaker monsters then deal 2400 damage after the battle phase.  You can also bring out any of the level 7+ monsters then discard or tribute 1 dragon using Claw of Hermos to bring out Red-Eyes Black Dragon Sword which gives the equiped monster 1000 attack and 500 defense for every Dragon on the either player's field or graveyard.

deck_excerpt: The best Darklord Deck ever made. If you want to try your luck with a darklord that rarely hand blocks you, and wins many extreme duels try this one.
deck_description: With this deck i have won against Blue Eyes, Dark Magician, Red Eyes, deskbots, banish deck, etc. This deck has the answers for pretty much every deck if you play your cards right, but it still has it limits. HOWEVER the limits are very high, i have been in duels were both my opponent and I gain 30,000+ life points, and 10,000+ attack points. This is primary because, my deck focus on stealing the power of my enemy, and using it against them. Without the right hand, you may still lose against fast decks like Fluffal or the new link decks, but your win lose streak will be about even, but with more wins. I love playing with this deck, because of how fun the duels can be, so I hope one of you duelers give it a try :D.

This resembles Yugi's Deck used in Battle City.  I used yugioh.wikia.com to make this deck as accurate as possible.  * I didn't use any Anime exclusive cards.  * I couldn't add all of the cards that were shown in episode 85 when Yugi was rebuilding his deck (Silver Fang, Feral Imp, Cyber Jar etc.), because I didn't want to exceed 40 cards in the Main Deck as the Side Deck was already full, so I only used the most important ones.  *Feel free to edit the Deck as you wish.

This resembles Kaiba's Deck used in Battle City.  I used yugioh.wikia.com to make this deck as accurate as possible.  * I replaced some Anime exclusive cards, with real cards that have a similar effect:  (On the left side are the Anime cards on the right side the card I replaced it with)  *Absorb Spell -> Spell Absorption (nearly identical artwork, but different effect)  *Card Guard -> Half Shut  *Attack Guidance Armor -> Call of the Earthbound     *Feel free to edit the Deck as you wish.

This resembles Jonouchi's Deck used in Battle City.  I used yugioh.wikia.com to make this deck as accurate as possible.  * I didn't use any Anime exclusive cards.  *I left "Insect Queen" and "The Legendary Fisherman" in the Side Deck to make this deck more playable.  *I still added the Red-Eyes, despite him giving the card to Yugi, but you can remove it if you want.  *He forgot to remove "Parasite Paracide" before his duel vs. Kajiki, after Haga's minion added it to his deck.  *He used a Spell Card with the name "Energy Drain", but it has a different artwork and effect.  *Feel free to edit the Deck as you wish.

deck_description: Basically, Fur Hire can link summon very easily, so after flooding the board, just link summon a Predaplant Verte Anaconda, summon Dragun of Red Eyes and continue to do your Fur Hire tricks.
